OL,3,CJubilation for Cardiff City after
OL,4,Csecuring promotion back to the
OL,5,CChampionship
OL,7,FSkipper Rubin Colwill gave City a 1-0
OL,8,Fhalf-time lead, courtesy of a back-
OL,9,Fpost header in the 40th minute, and
OL,10,FOmari Kellyman doubled their advantage
OL,11,F10 minutes into the second half.
OL,13,FDaniel Kyerewaa cut the deficit in the
OL,14,F73rd minute but defender Perry Ng
OL,15,Fsealed the win four minutes from the
OL,16,Fend.
OL,18,FReading defender Jeriel Dorsett
OL,19,Fscooped over from close range and
OL,20,Fwinger Kyerewaa drove narrowly wide as
OL,21,Fthe Royals started well.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/4
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1776679573
OL,3,CJubilation for Cardiff City after
OL,4,Csecuring promotion back to the
OL,5,CChampionship
OL,7,FBut Colwill broke the deadlock by
OL,8,Fsending a well-directed header past
OL,9,Fhome goalkeeper Joel Pereira, from
OL,10,FRyan Wintle's cross.
OL,12,FThe Bluebirds added a second when
OL,13,FKellyman broke the offside trap and
OL,14,Fcalmly slotted home his ninth goal of
OL,15,Fthe campaign.
OL,17,FThe hosts reduced the deficit when
OL,18,FKyerewaa netted on the follow-up after
OL,19,FCardiff keeper Nathan Trott could only
OL,20,Fparry Lewis Wing's powerful free-kick.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/4
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
